There’s excitement on KwaZulu-Natal’s coast as sardines make their annual run. DURBAN - KwaZulu-Natal's famous sardine run is under way. Fishermen and holidaymakers crowded the beach on Sunday to take photos and videos of their arrival and netting. Experts predicted large shoals would move past the KwaZulu-Natal South Coast. READ: Excitement as sardines arrive in Durban Large shoals of the small fish have been sighted off Amanzimtoti, south of Durban. The public can freely watch the spectacle but permits are needed for anglers and those casting nets.